    "This lemma has been known since the 50s (Kullback, 1959, Exercise 8.28) in the case of a finite Θ, but the general case is due to Donsker and Varadhan (1976).",
    "Lemma 2.2 (Donsker and Varadhan's variational formula).",
    "For any measurable, bounded function h: Θ → R we have:",
    "Moreover, the supremum with respect to ρ in the right-hand side is reached for the Gibbs measure π h defined by its density with respect to π:",
    "E ϑ∼π e h(ϑ)."
